---
title: Veggie-Loaded Orzo and Sausage with Zucchini, Tomatoes, and Bell Pepper
description: With this recipe, we gave ourselves a challenge: to see how many veggies we could tuck into orzo pasta before going into veggie overload. As it turns out, it might be impossible to have too many veggies. But we settled on a pretty solid bunch—half-moons of succulent zucchini, strands of sweet bell pepper, and juicy grape tomato baubles. Plus, there are bits of Italian sausage to keep things nice and meaty.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5b4f732dae08b526114d0cb6-44acbf88.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/veggie-loaded-orzo-and-sausage-5b4f732dae08b526114d0cb6-2c473e9a.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/veggie-loaded-orzo-and-sausage-5b4f732dae08b526114d0cb6
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 84 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1120 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of @salt{for water} water to a boil. Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely chop @red onion{1}. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise, then slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Core and seed @bell pepper{1}, then thinly slice. Remove @sweet Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from casings.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside, keeping as much grease in pan as possible.

Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add onion and zucchini. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add @orzo pasta{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{7-9%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve 1/4 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Add bell pepper and garlic to pan with zucchini. Cook, tossing, until bell pepper softens, ~{2-4%minutes}. Add tomatoes and cook, tossing, until warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Toss orzo and sausage into pan. Stir in half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @lemon juice{2%pack} to taste, and a splash of pasta water. Add more water as needed to loosen. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide orzo mixture between plates, then garnish with parsley and remaining Parmesan.

> This recipe challenges us to see how many veggies we can tuck into orzo pasta before going
> into veggie overload. We settled on a pretty solid bunch—half-moons of succulent zucchini,
> strands of sweet bell pepper, and juicy grape tomato baubles. Plus, there are bits of Italian
> sausage to keep things nice and meaty.